claim.claim-text:
1. A gaming machine comprising:
an input device for starting a basic game;
a display configured to display a plurality of symbol arrays; and
a controller configured to execute processing operations of:
(a) based on an input to the input device, randomly determining symbols to be displayed for a player when scrolling of the plurality of symbol arrays stops and then starting a basic game;
(b) scrolling the plurality of symbol arrays that are displayed on the display;
(c) based on a result of the random determination, sequentially stopping the scrolling of the plurality of symbol arrays;
(d) after the scrolling of the plurality of symbol arrays is stopped, when at least one predetermined symbol is displayed, migrating to a bonus game, said bonus game being carried out automatically without user participation, and then re-scrolling the plurality of symbol arrays;
(e) in the bonus game, randomly displaying at least one specific bonus symbol that can be employed in place of another symbol, so as to be substituted for any of a plurality of symbols;
(f) sequentially stopping the re-scrolling of the plurality of symbol arrays in the bonus game; and
(g) awarding a prize according to the number of the specific bonus symbols that are displayed in the bonus game.

2. A gaming machine comprising:
an input device for starting a basic game;
a display configured to display a plurality of symbol arrays; and
a controller configured to execute processing operations of:
(a) based on an input to the input device, randomly determining symbols to be displayed for a player when scrolling of the plurality of symbol arrays stops and then starting a basic game;
(b) scrolling the plurality of symbol arrays that are displayed on the display;
(c) based on a result of the random determination, sequentially stopping the scrolling of the plurality of symbol arrays;
(d) after the scrolling of the plurality of symbol arrays is stopped, when at least one predetermined symbol is displayed, migrating to a bonus game, said bonus game being carried out automatically without user participation, and then re-scrolling the plurality of symbol arrays;
(e) in the bonus game, displaying at least one specific bonus symbol that can be employed in place of another symbol, so as to be substituted for any of a plurality of symbols, by means of a random determination to be made by the bonus game;
(f) sequentially stopping the re-scrolling of the plurality of symbol arrays in the bonus game; and
(g) awarding a prize according to the number of the specific bonus symbols that are displayed in the bonus game.

3. A gaming machine comprising:
an input device for starting a basic game;
a display configured to display a plurality of symbol arrays; and
a controller configured to execute processing operations of:
(a) based on an input to the input device, randomly determining symbols to be displayed for a player when scrolling of the plurality of symbol arrays stops and then starting a basic game;
(b) scrolling the plurality of symbol arrays that are displayed on the display;
(c) based on a result of the random determination, sequentially stopping the scrolling of the plurality of symbol arrays;
(d) after the scrolling of the plurality of symbol arrays is stopped, when at least one predetermined symbol is displayed, migrating to a bonus game, said bonus game being carried out automatically without user participation, and then re-scrolling the plurality of symbol arrays;
(e) in the bonus game, executing in advance a random determination of whether or not to display at least one specific bonus symbol that can be employed in place of another symbol, so as to be substituted for any of a plurality of symbols, as to a total number of games that are executed in the bonus game;
(f) sequentially stopping the re-scrolling of the plurality of symbol arrays in the bonus game;
(g) based on the random determination in (e), displaying the at least one specific bonus symbol so as to be substituted for any of the plurality of symbols in the bonus game; and
(h) awarding a prize according to the number of the specific bonus symbols that are displayed in the bonus game.

4. A gaming machine comprising:
an input device for starting a basic game;
a display configured to display a plurality of symbol arrays; and
a controller configured to execute processing operations of:
(a) based on an input to the input device, randomly determining symbols to be displayed for a player when scrolling of the plurality of symbol arrays stops and then starting a basic game;
(b) scrolling the plurality of symbol arrays that are displayed on the display;
(c) based on a result of the random determination, sequentially stopping the scrolling of the plurality of symbol arrays;
(d) after the scrolling of the plurality of symbol arrays is stopped, when at least one predetermined symbol is displayed, migrating to a bonus game, said bonus game being carried out automatically without user participation, and then re-scrolling the plurality of symbol arrays;
(e) in the bonus game, displaying at least one specific bonus symbol that can be employed in place of another symbol, so as to be substituted for any of a plurality of symbols, by means of a random determination to be made by the bonus game;
(f) sequentially stopping the re-scrolling of the plurality of symbol arrays in the bonus game;
(g) in the bonus game, randomly determining whether or not to migrate to another bonus game, and migrating to another bonus game based on said random determination in (g); and
(h) once all bonus games have been completed, awarding a prize according to the total number of the specific bonus symbols that were displayed in all of the bonus games.
